data.prompt:
We're building a new feature for Dylan's outreach dashboard. Read the request below, then write a tight plan: (1) what the user-visible outcome is in one sentence, (2) the files that will likely change, (3) the order of work (data model -> API -> UI -> tests), (4) anything risky or unclear. Keep it under 200 words.

Feature request:
{{message}}

Based on the plan below, design the structure: data model changes (Supabase tables/columns/migrations), API surface (routes + request/response shapes), and any shared lib helpers. Write enough detail that a developer agent can implement directly. Reference real paths under /root/projects/outreach-dashboard.

Plan:
{{plan}}

Original request:
{{message}}

Implement the UI portion of this feature. Use Next.js App Router, Tailwind, shadcn/ui, and the patterns already in src/components and src/app/(dashboard). Write the actual files. Wire to the API surface defined in the structure. Output a short list of files created/modified.

Plan:
{{plan}}

Structure:
{{structure}}

Original request:
{{message}}

Implement the server portion: API routes under src/app/api, any new Supabase migrations under migrations/, shared helpers under src/lib. Write the actual files. The frontend agent already wrote the UI based on the same structure spec, so keep request/response shapes consistent.

Plan:
{{plan}}

Structure:
{{structure}}

Frontend changes:
{{frontend_changes}}

Original request:
{{message}}

Write tests for the new feature and run them. Cover the happy path plus 1-2 obvious edge cases. If anything fails, fix it. Run `npx tsc --noEmit` clean too. Return: tests added, run results, and any fixes applied.

Frontend changes:
{{frontend_changes}}

Backend changes:
{{backend_changes}}

